Name: Unseen Heights
Description: Reach for the stars.
Instructions: Go where even the editor fears to tread.
Solution: Pass any map that is 100*+. NOTE: This medal is doable on converts, so long as the star rating of the convert is 100*+.

Name: Astronomic
Description: Precision machinery.
Instructions: Celestial coordinates: 284-905.
Solution: FC any 6*+ difficulty of any map by the artist II-L. NOTE: There is a second (currently broken) way to get this medal that requires an FC on any 5*+ difficulty of any map by the artist II-L using the ScoreV2 mod; this conditional currently does not work, and there is no estimated timeframe for when it will be fixed.

Name: Star Power
Description: AND I'LL DO IT AGAIN.
Instructions: When an encore just isn't enough.
Solution: SS any map without HR, then SS any 4*+ map with HR. NOTE: You MUST get the scores back-to-back; if you mess up at any point on the second map or retry the map partway through, you must restart the medal from the beginning. NOTE: You may use any other difficulty increasing mods alongside NM/HR, but said mods must be present on both plays. For example, HD → HDHR works, but NM → HDHR does not. NOTE: If you are trying to achieve this medal in Taiko, for complicated reasons, the second map you play must have zero spinners or drumrolls for the medal to work.

Name: Hybrid Hyperion
Description: Manifold conqueror.
Instructions: You proteans should show off more.
Solution: Set an A-rank play (or higher) on a 4*+ difficulty in all 4 gamemodes within a hybrid set. NOTE: A "hybrid set" is one beatmap that has difficulties rank in all four gamemodes. Examples of this kind of map are listed on this page in the "Beatmaps" section to the right. NOTE: Each score must be the most recent play in their respective game mode. NOTE: For the first three plays, mods will not affect the SR the game is checking; for example, if your first play is a 3* map, and you put DT on to make it 4*+, it will still be considered 3* and will not work for this medal.

Name: Divination Break
Description: So cold...
Instructions: The frozen thread shattered.
Solution: FC any 5*+ difficulty of Yooh - Ice Angel, but miss the very first (or very last) note. NOTE: This is true for all FC-based medals, but is especially pertinent for this medal in particular -- an "FC" in this context means you cannot miss any sliderends. In the case of this medal, your play must have exactly 1 less than the maximum combo of the map.

Name: Unwilted
Description: Vivid recollection of a forgotten memory.
Instructions: Flourish anew like it was yesterday.
Solution: FC any 4*+ map, first try, with the following criteria: · You have not played that difficulty of the map in at least one year (including fails) · You have previously FC'd the map · You are using the same mod combo as a previous FC NOTE: If you fail in obtaining the FC and did not overwrite your score, you can wait 24 hours for another attempt on that difficulty of the map.

Name: Jackpot
Description: Lucky sevens is a mild understatement.
Solution: Complete a map with a score above 100,000, where every digit of the score is the same (222,222 / 7,777,777 / 99,999,999 / etc). Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed.

Name: Quick Draw
Description: It's high noon.
Solution: Be the first to submit a score on any ranked or qualified map.

Name: Obsessed
Description: COMPLETION AT ALL COSTS.
Solution: Retry a map 100 or more times and then pass it all within 24 hours. NOTE: Each 'retry' must have at least 10,000 score for it to count as a play.

Name: Nonstop
Description: Breaks? What are those?
Solution: Full combo any map that has a drain time of 8:41 or longer (before mods). NOTE: Make sure you are looking at the map's drain time and not the total runtime! You can see a map's drain time by hovering your mouse over the runtime on the map's beatmap page. (Yes, it is actually 8:41, we do not know why lol)

Name: Jack of All Trades
Description: Good at everything.
Solution: Get 5000+ playcount in each of the four gamemodes (standard / taiko / mania / catch the beat).

Name: I Can See The Top
Description: Your dedication has paid off. Welcome to the top 50,000!
Solution: Reach at least rank 50.000 in the pp rankings.

Name: The Gradual Rise
Description: There's no stopping you, is there? Welcome to the top 10,000!
Solution: Reach at least rank 10.000 in the pp rankings.

Name: Scaling Up
Description: Welcome to the top 5,000. Never give up!
Solution: Reach at least rank 5.000 in the pp rankings.

Name: Approaching The Summit
Description: Pro tier. Welcome to the top 1,000!
Solution: Reach at least rank 1.000 in the pp rankings.

Name: Time Dilation
Description: Longer is shorter when all is said and done.
Instructions: Time often flies when one is having fun, though rarely does it last forever.
Solution: Pass any map that is 8 minutes or longer (after mods), using either of the mods above. NF is not allowed, but all other non-conflicting difficulty reducing mods are. NOTE: This means the map must be at least 12 minutes before DT/NC is applied. NOTE: Make sure you are looking at the map's drain time and not the total runtime! You can see a map's drain time by hovering your mouse over the runtime on the map's beatmap page.

Name: To The Core
Description: In for a penny, in for a pound. Pounding bass, that is.
Instructions: Double negatives sometimes do make a positive.
Solution: Pass any map that contains 'nightcore' in the title or artist name, using either of the mods above.

Name: Prepared
Description: Do it for real next time.
Instructions: Preparation is key for all successful endeavours.
Solution: FC any map, using NF.

Name: Reckless Abandon
Description: Throw it all to the wind.
Instructions: Do it just because you can, even if the stakes are high.
Solution: FC any 3*+ map, using the mods above.

Name: Lights Out
Description: The party's just getting started.
Instructions: Set the mood.
Solution: Pass any map, using the mods above.

Name: Camera Shy
Description: Stop being cute.
Instructions: Uguu.
Solution: FC any map, using the mods above.

Name: The Sum Of All Fears
Description: Unfortunate.
Instructions: The end comes when you least expect it.
Solution: FC any map, but miss the very last (or very first) note.

Name: Hour Before The Dawn
Description: Eleven skies of everlasting sunrise.
Instructions: The night where we belong.
Solution: FC any difficulty of ginkiha - EOS.

Name: Slow And Steady
Description: Win the race, or start again.
Instructions: Take your time.
Solution: FC any 3*+ map, using the mods above.

Name: No Time To Spare
Description: Places to be, things to do.
Instructions: Think fast, click fast, be fast.
Solution: FC any map, using DT, that is 30 seconds or shorter (after mods).

Name: Sognare
Description: A dream in stop-motion, soon forever gone.
Instructions: "I saw three spires all around, and a world in halted time.."
Solution: Pass LeaF - Evanescent, using HT. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed.

Name: Realtor Extraordinaire
Description: An acre-wide stride.
Instructions: The wrong kind of house.
Solution: FC any difficulty of cYsmix - House With Legs, using the mods above.

Name: Impeccable
Description: Speed matters not to the exemplary.
Instructions: Simply superb.
Solution: Pass any 4*+ map, using the mods above.

Name: Aeon
Description: In the mire of thawing time, memory shall be your guide.
Instructions: When time runs slow and sight fails you, how will you succeed?
Solution: FC any map that was ranked in 2011 or earlier, using the mods above. The map must be at least 4* and at least 3 minutes long after mods.

Name: Quick Maths
Description: Beats per minute over... this isn't quick at all!
Instructions: Where x equals beats per minute, and a variable unknown...
Solution: Get exactly 34 misses on any difficulty of <i>Function Phantom - Variable<i>.

Name: Kaleidoscope
Description: So many pretty colours. Most of them red.
Instructions: See the tiny colours up through the tube up close and personal, and slow right down.
Solution: Pass The Flashbulb - DIDJ PVC [EX III] with 80% accuracy or higher, using the mods above.

Name: Valediction
Description: One last time.
Instructions: Time stood still as we waved farewell.
Solution: Pass a_hisa - Alexithymia | Lupinus | Tokei no Heya to Seishin Sekai with 90% accuracy or higher. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed.

Name: Ten To One
Description: From one extreme to another.
Instructions: From a marathon to a sprint.
Solution: Pass a map that is 10 minutes or longer, then pass a map that is 1 minute or shorter. NOTE: DT is allowed, just make sure that the map is longer than 10 minutes before you apply mods. NOTE: Make sure you are looking at the map's drain time and not the total runtime! You can see a map's drain time by hovering your mouse over the runtime on the map's beatmap page.

Name: Exquisite
Description: Indubitably.
Instructions: Do it once with true calibre, then do it again.
Solution: FC two different 3*+ maps in a row, using either of the mods above.

Name: Persistence Is Key
Description: Don't let your dreams be dreams.
Instructions: Don't give up!
Solution: Fail any difficulty of Thaehan - Never Give Up five times, and then pass it. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed. NOTE: Each failed play must have at least 10,000 score for it to count as a play.

Name: Mad Scientist
Description: The experiment... it's all gone!
Instructions: Become invisible.
Solution: Pass every difficulty of Thank You Scientist - Mr. Invisible, using HD. NOTE: Using DT is allowed. Using NF is not allowed, despite the category the medal is in.

Name: Tribulation
Description: Success is inevitable... eventually.
Instructions: Struggle and then stop.
Solution: Pass any map that you have 100+ playcount on and have not passed yet. NOTE: Due to some coding weirdness, if you go to a map you have over 100 playcount on, and play that difficulty in a converted gamemode (e.x. a standard map on taiko), it will count.

Name: Right On Time
Description: The first minute is always the hardest.
Instructions: Every hour's got sixty, but your timer only wants one.
Solution: Submit a score on Kola Kid - timer on the first minute of any hour (ex: 5:00pm, 6:00pm). NOTE: The play must END at this time, so make sure to time this properly! For example, a DT play will need to be started in the first half of :59, not started at :00. NOTE: The 'seconds' on the play do not matter, as long as you are within minute :00 of the hour.

Name: Replica
Description: One just like the other.
Instructions: Duplicate.
Solution: Get the same accuracy on two different difficulties of Zekk - Duplication. NOTE: Plays must be on same mapset and same gamemode. NOTE: This can only be done on the beatmaps to the right. No other ranked beatmps of the same artist and title give the medal.

Name: All Good
Description: Better now, thanks!
Instructions: You got this.
Solution: Set two scores on Carpool Tunnel - Better Now in a row. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed. NOTE: If you decide to use mods, you must use the same mods on both scores.

Name: Not Again
Description: Regret everything.
Instructions: You had it all, and then it was gone.
Solution: Get 1xMiss and 99%+ accuracy on ARForest - Regret.

Name: Deliberation
Description: The challenge remains.
Instructions: Turn a short challenge into a long one.
Solution: FC any ranked or loved map, with HT, that is 6*+ after mods. NOTE: Using additional mods (e.x. HTHR) is allowed.

Name: When You See It
Description: Three numbers which will haunt you forevermore.
Instructions: You don't need a hint for this one.
Solution: Pass any map by song artist "xi" with X7.27% accuracy (97.27%, 87.27%, etc.). NOTE: All mods are allowed. Note that there is also an artist named "Xi", with a capital X -- that is a different person and their maps do not count for this medal.

Name: Time Sink
Description: Rise from the depths into a new age.
Instructions: Descend into the fathoms, yesteryear and today.
Solution: Submit a score on both awp's 2009 and Camo's 2021 mapsets of Alestorm - Keelhauled (in a row, in that order). Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed. NOTE: You MUST get the scores back-to-back, and the second one must be a pass; if you fail at any point on the second map, you must restart the medal from the beginning.

Name: You're Here Forever
Description: We knew you'd be back.
Instructions: Touch grass.
Solution: Pass any map in any gamemode after not having played that gamemode for 2 or more weeks. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed. NOTE: You must have over 2,500 playcount in the gamemode that you play upon coming back, otherwise it will not work. NOTE: Make sure your submitted play is a pass (no restarts), otherwise the fail will count as a submitted play, and you will have to wait another 2 weeks.

Name: Hospitality
Description: Welcome.
Instructions: From guest, to host.
Solution: Play a guest difficulty of any mapper, then pass a different map by the same mapper. Using NF is not allowed, despite the category the medal is in. NOTE: The second map you play can be any map, guest diff or host diff, but the first one must be specifically a guest difficulty.

Name: True North
Description: Where they tread, you go.
Instructions: Seek your favourite creator to lead the way.
Solution: Play 10 maps in a row from the same mapper. All plays must be on different beatmap sets. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed. NOTE: Guest difficulties count for the person credited for mapping it, not for the host of the mapset.

Name: Superfan
Description: THIS IS MY JAM.
Instructions: AHHHHHH THEY'RE MY OSHI.
Solution: Play 10 maps in a row from the same artist. All plays must be on different beatmap sets. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed.

Name: Resurgence
Description: A flame rekindled.
Instructions: From the ashes, blaze bright.
Solution: Play any map that contains the word "ashes" in the song title, then pass any difficulty of Panda Eyes & Teminite - Immortal Flame (feat. Anna Yvette). Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed.

Name: Clarity
Description: And yet in our memories, you remain crystal clear.
Instructions: A distorted reality and our own intersect.
Solution: Pass rrtyui's mapset of Camellia vs Akira Complex - Reality Distortion. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed.

Name: Autocreation
Description: Absolute rule.
Instructions: One is all.
Solution: Pass any map in which the artist and the host of the mapset are the same person. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed.

Name: Festive Fever
Description: And the jingle bells never stop.
Instructions: Well, eventually they do if you aren't careful enough.
Solution: During the December holiday season, pass one difficulty on each mapset of every osu! original christmas song. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed. NOTE: Despite being listed as an all-mode medal, this medal is only achievable in osu!standard. This medal is only achievable while the osu! Christmas seasonal updates are active; it will next be possible to achieve this medal some time around December 2024.

Name: Value your Identity
Description: As perfect as you are.
Instructions: In the end, you'll know what to do.
Solution: Achieve a score on any map where your max combo is equal to the last 3 digits of your User ID. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed. NOTE: If your User ID ends in 000, you need to get a 1,000 combo score, regardless of the fourth-last digit in your ID.

Solution: Pass any 9 star map (calculated with mods) without using EZ/NF/HT mods.

Description: Fevered is your passion, extraordinary is your skill.
Instructions: Approach the limit of human endurance, and pass a 10 star map.
Solution: Pass any 10 star map (calculated with mods) without using EZ/NF/HT mods.

Name: Unstoppable
Description: Holy shit.
Instructions: Reaching the limits of mortal skill.
Solution: Pass any map with AR11 OD11 HP11 and over 260BPM. Note: To get this, the map must be AR8+, OD8+, HP8+, and 174+ BPM, and you must use DT+HR (+HD, optionally).

Name: Is This Real Life?
Description: You did NOT just pull that off.
Instructions: The absolute height of perfection.
Solution: FC any map with AR11 OD11 HP11 and over 260BPM. Note: To get this, the map must be AR8+, OD8+, HP8+, and 174+ BPM, and you must use DT+HR (+HD, optionally).

Name: Thrill of the Chase
Description: My heart's beating, my hands are shaking, and I'm STILL clicking.
Instructions: Is there anything better than the hunt? Such a classic pursuit.
Solution: FC cYsmix - Classic Pursuit [Advanced], using DT, or [Normal], using DTHR.

Name: True Torment
Description: It lasts forever.
Instructions: Note the ghosts.
Solution: Pass Helblinde - The Solace of Oblivion with 70%+ accuracy.

Name: Skylord
Description: Never miss a wingbeat.
Instructions: Flight among the sky requires nothing but perfection.
Solution: SS James Portland - Sky [Master].

Name: Vantage
Description: There we stood, where the spires pierced the sky, and dreamed of the future to come.
Instructions: Where ground was broken to critical acclaim.
Solution: Pass Culprate & Au5 - Impulse.

Name: Not Bluffing
Description: Did that with my eyes closed.
Instructions: It's not arrogance if you can live up to it.
Solution: PFC onumi - ARROGANCE [Hard] or higher with the mods above.

Name: Final Boss
Description: Game over.
Instructions: Let the credits roll.
Solution: Pass Yooh - RPG [Divinity] with 92%+ accuracy.

Name: Beast Mode
Description: Unleash the animal within!
Instructions: Go absolutely feral.
Solution: Pass meganeko - Feral [Veracious] with 98%+ accuracy.

Name: Mortal Coils
Description: Never one without the other.
Instructions: Prisoners of flesh in an unending apocalypse.
Solution: Pass any difficulty of the ranked mapsets of Fleshgod Apocalypse - The Deceit and Fleshgod Apocalypse - The Violation.

Name: Dark Familiarity
Description: No mistakes, no witnesses.
Instructions: Don't second guess yourself.
Solution: FC Maduk ft. Veela - Ghost Assassin (Hourglass Bonusmix) [Lumiere], using the mods above.

Name: Iron Will
Description: A legacy of broken bonds, remade.
Instructions: Step forth, and master three years of titan-ending tests.
Solution: Pass all of the osu! World Cup Grand Finals custom tiebreaker maps from 2020 to 2022.

Name: Causality
Description: Definitely not for casuals.
Instructions: Flee from the future.
Solution: Pass KNOWER - Time Traveler with 75%+ accuracy. NOTE: Remember to enable storyboard and enjoy the experience!

Name: Abrogation
Description: Endure not the imposition of celestial law.
Instructions: Return to whence the rules were first broken.
Solution: Pass aran - Graces of Heaven with 72%+ accuracy.

Name: Internment
Description: Stained in the hues of madness, they rage within a four-walled jail.
Instructions: Bask in the shade of an ailing mind.
Solution:
On any 'Insane' difficulty (4.0* - 5.29*) of Frums - theyaremanycolors, set three plays in a row that have combos equal to the R, G, and B values of the difficulty indicator (on the osu! website) for the map you are playing. The possible combinations are as follows:
PlayCombo (vanchanicalinsane)Combo (celinsane)
1st255x243x
2nd104x76x
3rd108x133x
You can find an explanation to the solution in the pinned comments below. NOTE: You MUST get the scores back-to-back, and the third one must be a pass; if you overcombo at any point on the second or third play, fail the third play, or fail to reach the max combo requirement for the second or third score, you must restart the medal from the beginning. NOTE: Difficulty reduction mods and failing are both allowed for the first two plays, despite the category the medal is in.

Name: Don't let the bunny distract you!
Description: The order was indeed, not a rabbit.
Solution: FC any difficulty of Chatmonchy - Make Up! Make Up!.

Name: S-Ranker
Description: Accuracy is really underrated.
Solution: Get five S (or SS) ranks on different maps within 24 hours. NOTE: S+ and SS+ ranks (silver S and SS ranks, which are done when using HD or FL) also work.

Name: Most Improved
Description: Now THAT is improvement.
Solution: Get a D rank with more than 100,000 score, and then get an A rank or better on the same map within 24 hours after that play. Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed.

Name: Non-stop Dancer
Description: Can you still feel your feet after that?
Solution: Pass Yoko Ishida - paraparaMAX I with over 3,000,000 score. NOTE: NF is not allowed, but all other difficulty reducing mods are.

Name: Consolation Prize
Description: Well, it could be worse.
Solution: Get a D rank on any map with a play that is above 100,000 score. Using any mods is not allowed. NOTE: In addition to the above, you must have achieved the Most Improved medal before you are able to achieve this medal.

Name: Challenge Accepted
Description: Oh, you're ON.
Solution: Pass any approved map. NOTE: This medal is slightly janky and can occasionally not work; nobody knows why. If this medal does not work for you, please consider joining the Exploring Incomplete Medal Solutions forum post in osu! Medal Hunters server, so you can help us figure out why!

Name: Stumbler
Description: No regrets.
Solution: FC any map with less than 85% accuracy.

Name: Afterimage
Description: But a glimpse of its true self.
Instructions: Always coming behind the original image.

NOTE: For whatever map you decide to do this on, the sum of the number of circles, double the number of sliders, and triple the number of spinners must be at least 400. Only god knows why this is a requirement.

Description: That wasn't easy at all!

Name: Equilibrium
Description: Balance in all things.
Instructions: Seek the middle ground.

Name: In Memoriam
Description: In loving memory of your sanity, long forgotten.

Name: Sanguine

Name: Banana Republic
Description: Potassium overdose.
Instructions: The more may not always be the merrier.
Solution: Set an SS on any map, then set a play that has less accuracy but a higher total score. NOTE: This is only possible by outspinning your old score by collecting more bananas. Make sure that your first play collects as few bananas as possible. NOTE: If you decide to use mods, you must use the same mods on both scores. NOTE: You MUST get the scores back-to-back; if you mess up at any point on the second map or retry the map partway through, you must restart the medal from the beginning.

Name: Dexterity
Description: True savants are flexible.
Instructions: Don't go all in on one stat.
Solution: Get a 95%+ play on two different difficulties of the same mapset that have different keycounts from eachother (e.x. 4K and 7K). Difficulty reduction mods, including NF, are allowed. NOTE: You can use keymods to change the keycount of a convert map. For example, a 4K convert difficulty with the 5K mod applied will count as 5K. Keep in mind that you still have to play two different difficulties if you do this; you cannot play 4K and 5K on the same difficulty. NOTE: This medal is slightly janky and can occasionally not work; nobody knows why. If this medal does not work for you, please consider joining the Exploring Incomplete Medal Solutions forum post in osu! Medal Hunters server! so you can help us figure out why!
